    "The assumption of normal distribution of the residuals (E i ∼ N(0, σ 2)) is confirmed by the Anderson-Darling test [123] with a p-value equal to 6.6 % as well as through the QQ plot of residuals versus Normal distribution showing points lie on a line.",
    "Concerning homoscedasticity, a condition in which the residual variance is constant across all the model predictions, there are no visible patterns in the scatter plot of residuals versus predicted ESG scores.",
    "The same condition is confirmed by the scatter plot of the pre-dicted ESG scores versus the actual scores.",
    "However, a slight overestimation trend might be spotted for ESG scores below 50, showing a limit of our predictors for interpreting these low scores.",
